title: Bridgewater Canal
initial_description: Francis Egerton, 3rd Duke of Bridgewater, needed a better way to get coal from his mines near Worsley & Manchester...
sidebar_text: See if you can connect Worsley with the Mersey and Irwell Navigation in Manchester.

DisplayText.text:
Despite the existance of the Mersey and Irwell Navigation, James Brindley - the original engineer for the Bridgewater Canal - managed to get royal assent for an extension to the canal all the way to Runcorn.
This extension would go through a variety of towns, before ending at Mersey.
DisplayText.title: Extending from Manchester to Runcorn

events.SetSidebar: Build an extension connecting Sale, Altrincham, Lymm, Appleton and Runcorn to our canal.

DisplayText.text: In 1795, the Duke was able to approve an extension connecting the coal mines near Leigh to the canal, and from there to Manchester.
DisplayText.title: Extending from Worsley to Leigh

events.SetSidebar: Build an extension connecting Leigh to the Bridgewater Canal
